         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">South-Yarra, ¶  15/1/95. ¶ The honorable Sir William Clarke, Bart., LL.D., M.L.C. &amp;c. ¶  ¶ The thistle, of which you sent a specimen, dear Sir William, is the British Shore-Thistle (Carduus pycnocepha...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.01.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William John Clarke</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Archives, Silesian College, Rupertswood, Sunbury, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">South-Yarra,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Melbourne.</p>
               </note> 15/1/95.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The honorable Sir William Clarke, Bart., LL.D., M.L.C. &amp;c.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The thistle, of which you sent a specimen, dear Sir William, is the British Shore-Thistle (<name key="Carduus%20pycnocephalus">Carduus pycnocephalus</name>). As it is flowering under ordinary circumstances only once from the same root, this plant can be subdued by cutting it down before seeding; but the cut portions need heaping together and being burnt soon afterwards, otherwise seeds might still mature from the cut plants.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me to offer to her Ladyship and yourself and your florishing family a happy new year. May therefore the new annual span of time, on which now we have entered, be replete with joy to all of you!</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, ﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽﷽; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Thistle, which produces year after year off-shoots from its roots, is the European perennial Thistle (<name key="Carduus%20arvensis">Carduus arvensis</name>). It is often called the Canadian Thistle, but it is not a native of the western hemisphere.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Carduus%20arvensis">Carduus arvensis</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Carduus%20pycnocephalus">Carduus pycnocephalus</name>
            </p>
         </div>
